
<html>
<head>
  <meta charset="utf-8">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width">
  <title>My Favourite Cartoon Character</title>

  <!-- External CSS -->
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="style.css">

  <!-- Internal CSS -->
  <style>
    body{
      background-color:black;
    }
    h1{
      color: white;
      font-size: 34px;
    }

    .fun-fact {
      color: white;
      font-weight: bold;
    }

    #special-message {
      color: white;
      font-size: 18px;
    }

    h2, h3 {
      color:white;
    }
  </style>
</head>
<body>

  <h1>My Favourite Cartoon Character</h1>

  <div id="character-card">

    <h2>Jerry the Mouse</h2>

    <p>
      Jerry is my favourite cartoon character because he is wise,
      speedy, and very funny.
    </p>

    <!-- Inline CSS -->
    <p style="color: white; font-size: 18px;">
      He uses his brain and takes advantage of his small size to solve problems in
      creative ways.
    </p>

    <h3>Character Details</h3>
    <ul style="color: white">
      <li class="detail">Name: Jerry</li>
      <li class="detail">Worst Enemy: Tom the Cat</li>
      <li class="detail">Favourite Food: Cheese</li>
      <li class="detail">Special Power: His wiseness</li>
    </ul><br>

    <p class="fun-fact">
      Fun Fact: Jerry the Mouse is a very mature mouse who likes to drink wine.
    </p><br>

    <p id="special-message">
      Jerry teaches us that size does not matter, but in fact what is in the inside does.
    </p>

  </div>

</body>
</html>
